<dl id="n13150k"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n13" href="#n13150k">N13 (VI.D.3)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n13all.htm#n13150k"> 150(k)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Can&apos;t repent / paranoia</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">In fact, the capacity for repentence is left out of Mr. Joyce&apos;s makeup. It is as <mark>impossible to convince Mr. Joyce that he is wrong about anything</mark> on which he has made up his mind as it is to convince <mark>a paranoiac</mark> of the unreality of his false beliefs. <small> Joseph Collins, <a name="JCDL2" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#JCDL2"><cite title="source">The Doctor Looks at Literature&ldquo;</cite></a> (1923) 57</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Raphael transcription: <a name="c05089k" href="c5all.htm#c05089k">VI.C.05:089(k)</a></mm></dd> </dd></dl>
